<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --cream: #FAF8F5;
    --ink: #222222;
    --ink-soft: #555555;
    --ink-muted: #999999;
    --terracotta: #F4511E;
    --terracotta-light: #FDE8E2;
    --border: rgba(34,34,34,0.12);
    --serif: 'Syne', system-ui, sans-serif;
    --sans: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    background: var(--cream);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  /* NAV */
  nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.25rem 3rem;
    background: var(--cream);
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .nav-name {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .nav-links a {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--terracotta); }

  /* HERO */
  .hero {
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: 0 3rem 5rem;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .hero-name {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 9vw, 8rem);
    line-height: 0.92;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .hero-name em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--terracotta);
  }

  .hero-descriptor {
    max-width: 560px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--terracotta);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .hero-image-wrap {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    width: 280px;
    height: 350px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .hero-image-placeholder {
    display: none;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--terracotta-light);
    border: 1px dashed var(--terracotta);
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* SECTIONS */
  section {
    padding: 6rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    height: 1.5px;
    width: 3rem;
    background: var(--terracotta);
  }

  /* CASE STUDY CHAPTER HEADER */
  .case-chapter {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 3rem;
    margin: 0 -3rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .case-chapter-alt {
    background: #F5F0EA;
  }

  .case-chapter-logo {
    height: 28px;
    width: auto;
    object-fit: contain;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .case-chapter-name {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .case-chapter-divider {
    height: 1px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .case-study-alt {
    background: #F5F0EA;
    margin: 0 -3rem;
    padding: 2.5rem 3rem;
  }

  /* ABOUT */
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-left {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
  }

  .about-right {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-image-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .about-image-wrap {
    width: 200px;
    aspect-ratio: 3/4;
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .about-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .about-image-placeholder {
    display: none;
    width: 220px;
    height: 293px;
    background: var(--terracotta-light);
    border: 1px dashed var(--terracotta);
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .about-headline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .about-headline em { font-style: italic; color: var(--terracotta); }

  .about-body p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .tag {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    border-radius: 100px;
  }

  /* WORK / CASE STUDIES */
  .work-intro {
    max-width: 600px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .case-study {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .case-chapter {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 3rem;
    margin: 0 -3rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .case-study:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  .case-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .case-number {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    line-height: 1;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .case-tag {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }

  .case-title {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .case-desc {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .case-placeholder {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 0.5px dashed var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .case-body {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .case-section-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .case-section-text {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .case-strategy-block {
    background: var(--terracotta-light);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--terracotta);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0 2px 2px 0;
  }

  .case-strategy-block .case-section-label { color: var(--terracotta); }

  .case-strategy-block .case-section-text {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .case-strategy-headline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .case-section-headline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* CULTURAL INTELLIGENCE */
  .ci-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .ci-card {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 2.5rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .ci-card:last-child {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .ci-card:last-child .ci-evidence-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 280px);
  }

  .ci-card:hover { background: var(--terracotta-light); }

  .ci-number {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .ci-headline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ci-body {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .ci-sowhat {
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .ci-sowhat-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .ci-sowhat-text {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .ci-evidence {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }

  .ci-evidence-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ci-evidence-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ci-evidence-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }

  .ci-evidence-item img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 4/5;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 2px;
    display: block;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .ci-evidence-item:hover img { opacity: 0.8; }

  .ci-evidence-caption {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    line-height: 1.4;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .ci-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  /* WRITING */
  .writing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .writing-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: block;
  }

  .writing-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--terracotta);
    background: rgba(244,81,30,0.05);
  }

  .writing-type {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .writing-title {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .writing-excerpt {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* CULTURAL OBSERVATIONS */
  .obs-list {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .obs-item {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .obs-item:hover { background: var(--terracotta-light); }

  .obs-signal {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .obs-title {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .obs-body {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* CONTACT / FOOTER */
  footer {
    padding: 5rem 3rem 3rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
  }

  .footer-cta {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .footer-cta em { font-style: italic; color: var(--terracotta); }

  .footer-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .footer-link {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .footer-link:hover { color: var(--terracotta); }

  .footer-bottom {
    padding: 1.5rem 3rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .footer-bottom p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* ANIMATIONS */
  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .hero-eyebrow { animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease both; }
  .hero-name { animation: fadeUp 0.6s 0.1s ease both; }
  .hero-descriptor { animation: fadeUp 0.6s 0.2s ease both; }

  /* MOBILE */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    nav { padding: 1rem 1.5rem; }
    .nav-links { gap: 1.25rem; }
    .hero, section { padding-left: 1.5rem; padding-right: 1.5rem; }
    .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }    .writing-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .obs-list { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .case-study { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
    footer { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 2.5rem; padding: 3rem 1.5rem 2rem; }
    .footer-links { align-items: flex-start; }
    .footer-bottom { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ============================================================
     EDIT GUIDE — only change text between > and <
     DO NOT change anything that looks like class="..." or style="..."
     ============================================================ -->

<!-- NAV — your name as it appears top-left -->
<nav>
  <a href="#" class="nav-name">Maddie Jacobson</a>
  <ul class="nav-links">
    <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
    <li><a href="#work">Case Studies</a></li>
    <li><a href="#writing">Writing</a></li>
    <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<!-- ============================================================
     HERO — the first thing people see
     ============================================================ -->
<div class="hero">
  <!-- EDIT: your name — the <br> just creates a line break, <em> makes text italic+orange -->
  <h1 class="hero-name">Maddie<br><em>Jacobson</em></h1>
  <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-top: 1rem; font-weight: 400;">Brand Strategist</p>
</div>

<!-- ============================================================
     ABOUT
     ============================================================ -->
<section id="about">
  <p class="section-label">About</p>
  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-left">
      <!-- EDIT: the large headline. <br> = line break, <em> = italic orange -->
      <h2 class="about-headline">Born in social.<br><em>Trained in people.</em><br>Fluent in culture.</h2>
      <div class="about-tags">
        <!-- EDIT: add, remove, or rename skill tags -->
        <span class="tag">Brand Strategy</span>
        <span class="tag">Cultural Intelligence</span>
        <span class="tag">Consumer Insight</span>
        <span class="tag">Social Strategy</span>
        <span class="tag">Psychology</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-right">
      <div class="about-image-col">
        <!-- EDIT: your photo -->
        <div class="about-image-wrap">
          <img src="https://i.imgur.com/kYZ3rCW.jpg" alt="Maddie Jacobson" class="about-image">
        </div>
        <!-- Fez photo -->
        <div style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          <img src="https://i.imgur.com/LjG9tJS.jpg" alt="Fez the pug" style="width: 200px; border-radius: 2px; display: block;">
          <p style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--ink-muted); margin-top: 0.35rem; letter-spacing: 0.04em;">(that's Fez)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-body">
        <!-- EDIT: your bio paragraphs -->
        <p>I'm a brand strategist born in social. A therapist in another life. And a cultural anthropologist at heart.</p>
        <p>I've learned that the real story isn't in what people say, but rather in what they do. My background in psychology trained me to look for why people behave the way they do, and gave me a framework for uncovering the motivations beneath the surface. Paired with my experience in social, I'm especially attuned to tension points in culture.</p>
        <p>I'm especially drawn to what people already feel but don't always articulate. That's where the most powerful insights tend to live. Psychology helps me understand why those feelings exist; social shows me how they play out day to day. Together, they ground my thinking in people, not process, resulting in insights that feel intuitive, real, and not overly engineered.</p>
        <p>I'm endlessly curious and easily obsessed. There's nothing I can't get excited about.</p>
        <p>When I'm not building strategic briefs, you'll find me hanging with my pug, Fez, making some sort of craft or DIY, or trying out a new restaurant.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================================
     STRATEGIC CASE STUDIES
     ============================================================ -->
<section id="work">
  <p class="section-label">Strategic Case Studies</p>

  <!-- CHAPTER HEADER: Barefoot -->
  <div class="case-chapter">
    <img src="https://i.imgur.com/gAWiMWi.png" alt="Barefoot Wines" class="case-chapter-logo">
    <span class="case-chapter-name">Barefoot Wines</span>
    <div class="case-chapter-divider"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- CASE STUDY 01 — Barefoot -->
  <div class="case-study">
    <div class="case-meta">
      <span class="case-number">01</span>
      <span class="case-tag">Brand Strategy</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="case-title">How can a wine brand with a reputation problem win in a declining category?</h3>
      <!-- EDIT: the answer / strategic provocation -->
      <p class="case-desc">Stop apologizing for being cheap. Start championing every occasion that doesn't need a fancy bottle.</p>
      <!-- EDIT: what you actually did on this project -->
      <p class="case-desc" style="margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--ink-muted);">Built monthly cultural intelligence decks — drawing from social, Mintel, and cultural observation — presented directly to the Barefoot client and fed back into creative briefs.</p>

      <div class="case-body">
        <!-- Each block = one section. Pattern: label → headline → body text -->

        <div>
          <!-- EDIT: section category label -->
          <p class="case-section-label">The Problem</p>
          <!-- EDIT: leading insight headline -->
          <p class="case-section-headline">A Category in Decline</p>
          <!-- EDIT: body copy -->
          <p class="case-section-text">Barefoot sits in a crowded, shrinking category. Gen Z drinks less than any generation before them — driven by the sober-curious movement, cannabis, and fewer reasons to gather. And within that declining market, Barefoot carries an extra burden: the reputation of cheap wine for people who don't know better.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="case-section-label">Cultural Tension</p>
          <p class="case-section-headline">Gen Z is redefining what counts as a special occasion.</p>
          <p class="case-section-text">Traditional milestones are fading. In their place, Gen Z is inventing their own — Nowhere To Wear It parties, Presentation Nights, couch hangs elevated to events. Economic uncertainty pushed them home, and they turned it into a culture: hyper-specific, deeply personal, and entirely self-made.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="case-section-label">Category Tension</p>
          <p class="case-section-headline">The wine category is moving in the wrong direction.</p>
          <p class="case-section-text">As Gen Z redefines celebration, wine brands are doubling down on aspiration — chasing premium occasions like the picnic, the bachelorette, the anniversary dinner — trying to shed the "cheap" label by attaching themselves to moments that feel worthy of a nice bottle. But in doing so, they've abandoned the everyday entirely. No one is owning the unspecial moments that define Gen Z.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- STRATEGY BLOCK — highlighted in terracotta, always goes last -->
        <div class="case-strategy-block">
          <p class="case-section-label">The Strategy</p>
          <!-- EDIT: your big strategy headline -->
          <p class="case-strategy-headline">Proudly own the Unspecial Occasion.</p>
          <!-- EDIT: supporting strategy copy -->
          <p class="case-section-text">Emptying the lint tray. Everyone hearted your group text. The friend who showed up with snacks, unprompted. These aren't accidents — they're the moments Gen Z is actually living in. While the category chases occasions worth dressing up for, Barefoot should own every occasion that isn't. Make any moment a Barefoot moment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

