      <h3 class="ci-headline">Death of the Dinner Table</h3>
      <p class="ci-body">For Gen Z in 2024, snacking isn't just about eating between meals — it's a lifestyle shift where snacks often replace traditional meals entirely. Valuing "little treats" as everyday indulgences, they want small, satisfying bites that offer moments of joy throughout the day. Sippable treats — smoothies, coffees, and milkshakes — have become snacks in their own right, offering quick, easy enjoyment. This continued shift reflects a broader trend toward flexible, casual eating where convenience and small moments of enjoyment lead the way, allowing activities to dictate meals rather than the reverse.</p>
